---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const log = [
  { date: '2020', entry: 'Lockdown. First lines of HTML from free Skillshare courses and a rabbit hole of YouTube tutorials — where the whole thing actually began.' },
  { date: '2022', entry: 'Made it official at NIIT — formal foundations in Java, SQL, and the HTML/CSS/JS trio.' },
  { date: '2023', entry: 'Flutter, deep in tutorial hell — a graveyard of half-finished courses, and the one I actually saw through: all 37 hours of Vandad\'s.' },
  { date: '2024-10', entry: 'Joined Decentralyne as a mobile developer — still there, still shipping.' },
  { date: '2025-07', entry: 'Industrial attachment at NNPC Engineering & Technical Company: piping, Plant 3D, clash reviews.' },
  { date: '2025-11', entry: 'Picked up a frontend role at Downtown — site + dashboard.' },
  { date: '2026-03', entry: 'Wrapped up Downtown. Shipped, handed over, moved on.' },
  { date: '2026', entry: 'SIWES placement at a Lagos data center — live electrical infrastructure, SOPs, SLDs. (current)' },
];
---

<Base
  title="About — Adefila Abdulmuiz"
  description="About Adefila Abdulmuiz — mechatronics engineering student at Bells University of Technology, mobile developer, and CAD practitioner in Lagos, Nigeria."
>
  <section class="intro">
    <div class="intro-text">
      <p class="label breadcrumb"><a href="/">~</a>/about</p>
      <h1>Engineer by degree.<br />Developer by compulsion.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Mechatronics is the degree you pick when you can't choose between machines
        and computers. I picked it precisely so I wouldn't have to choose — and then
        didn't choose anyway.
      </p>
    </div>
    <figure class="portrait">
      <div class="frame">
        <img
          src="/about-portrait.png"
          width="220"
          height="220"
          alt="Pixel-art portrait of Adefila Abdulmuiz"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
        />
        <span class="scan" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </div>
      <figcaption class="label">adefila.png</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section class="group">
    <h2 class="label" data-reveal>// the short version</h2>
    <div class="prose" data-reveal>
      <p>
        I'm a final-year Mechatronics Engineering student at Bells University of
        Technology, and for the last two years I've been running two careers in
        parallel: by day (officially), CAD and electrical engineering — piping
        models, lighting simulations, single-line diagrams, data-center
        documentation. By night (also officially), mobile and web development —
        Flutter and React Native apps in production, with real users and real
        crash reports.
      </p>
      <p>
        The useful side effect: I've become a translator. Engineering teams and
        software teams notoriously talk past each other, and I've sat on both
        sides of that conversation — close enough to the hardware to respect it,
        close enough to the codebase to ship it. Requirements written in
        engineer-speak come out the other end as working software, and vice
        versa.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="group">
    <h2 class="label" data-reveal>// the log</h2>
    <ol class="log">
      {
        log.map((item, i) => (
          <li data-reveal style={`--reveal-delay: ${i * 70}ms`}>
            <span class="date">[{item.date}]</span>
            <span class="entry">{item.entry}</span>
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="group">
    <h2 class="label" data-reveal>// education</h2>
    <div class="edu" data-reveal>
      <p>
        <strong>B.Eng Mechatronics Engineering</strong> — Bells University of
        Technology, Ogun, Nigeria.
      </p>
      <p class="muted">Currently in 400 level.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="group">
    <h2 class="label" data-reveal>// full disclosure</h2>
    <div class="prose" data-reveal>
      <p>
        I once launched a public learning series on LinkedIn called
        <em>"100 Days of Growth."</em> It lasted four days. In my defence, the
        growth was real — I just spent it building things instead of posting
        about building things. The series may return; the consistency arc is
        still in development.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <aside class="next" data-reveal>
    <p class="label">// where to next</p>
    <p>
      See the work: <a href="/software">./software</a> ·
      <a href="/engineering">./engineering</a> — or
      <a href="/contact">say hello</a>.
    </p>
  </aside>
</Base>

<style>
  .intro {
    padding-block: var(--space-6) var(--space-5);
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-5);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .intro-text {
    flex: 1 1 28rem;
  }

  .portrait {
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    justify-items: center;
  }

  .frame {
    position: relative;
    line-height: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--bg);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 4px var(--surface);
    transition: border-color var(--speed-fast) var(--ease);
  }

  .frame:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }

  .frame img {
    display: block;
    width: clamp(168px, 38vw, 220px);
    height: auto;
    image-rendering: pixelated;
  }

  .scan {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(
      to bottom,
      rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.22) 0px,
      rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.22) 1px,
      transparent 1px,
      transparent 3px
    );
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  h1 {
    margin-block: var(--space-3);
  }

  .lede {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
  }

  .group {
    padding-block: var(--space-4);
  }

  .prose {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .prose p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .prose em,
  .prose strong {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .log {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }

  .log li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 7rem 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    padding: var(--space-2) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--border);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }

  .date {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .entry {
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .edu {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }

  .muted {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }

  .next {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    border: 1px dashed var(--border);
    padding: var(--space-4);
  }

  .next p:last-child {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .log li {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0;
    }
  }
</style>
